{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14545].
  {panel}

At the moment, Confluence doesn't recognise the PNG format as an attachment type. Ideally, it should show the same icon as it would for a jpg, or for any image.

Note: There is a project underway to make the default attachment icon more generic so this problem will be more pronounced when PNGs don't look like images at all.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14513].
  {panel}

It would be good if the Page Tree plugin could use labels instead of a page as its root. An example:

{noformat}
{pagetree:label=IRC, Tip, Sheets}
{noformat}

This would directory all documents of a given label(s). For instance:

* IRC
** Page A
** Page B
* Tip
** Page A
* Sheets
** Page C

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14509].
  {panel}

Currently the actual chart is centre-justified within the axes, and this means that there is a random-sized gap between the y-axis and the first plotted point.
The bigger the chart, the bigger the potential gap.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14485].
  {panel}

When you watch a lot of spaces/pages and these are frequently updated/commented on you can be inundated with notifications. It would be a really nice feature if you could choose to receive these notifications immediately or daily.

The ability to set this at a page/space level would also be a huge bonus.

This is discussed further on this page: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DISC/Email+Notification+Storms+-+Alternatives

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14481].
  {panel}

Searching by last name in the People Directory returns 0 results. Search by first name returns results. This appears to be a "begins with" search and should really be a "contains" or "like" search. Should just be a slight adjustment to the SQL query.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14477].
  {panel}

The documentation says that you can create links to files located in one location on the server disk (/etc/scripts? I don't remember and can't find it now).  I would like to be able to specify directories on the server disk where attachments can reside and be linked into a page AND be able to specify a separate location for each space.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14475].
  {panel}

The page tree view javascript can be painfully slow, especially when working with over 2000 pages. Part of the slowness is that it hides the area to which a page has just been dragged and then re-sorts it after every page move. It would be great to have an option to load a page tree view that doesn't do that (I can close and re-open the sub-tree manually if I want to see it in sorted order).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14473].
  {panel}

None of the templates seem to have a very good display of the information at the bottom of each page (the labels, children, comments, and such). That content blends in too much with the body of the page and creates a confusing blob of information at the bottom of the page. It would be nice to have something somewhat like the "menubar" at the top of the page where each of these was obviously an additional section at the bottom with options to edit and hide/show. This would especially help with the comments if they were in a separate format more conducive to reading comment threads.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14472].
  {panel}

Improve the History in the user menu to show all recently visited pages (not searches, labels, bookmarks, or other types). This would improve the ability to jump between pages in different spaces or hierarchies.

Alternatively (I had this in another wiki), you could offer an option for a different breadcrumb trail that shows x recent pages visited instead of the hierarchy.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14471].
  {panel}

Add Contacts as a space object, much like Bookmarks are now. Include a macro to display a listing (filtered by label) or an individual entry. Each entry in the listing should have a link to export a vcard. Preferably, the Contact space section would have an option to import standard contact format(s).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14461].
  {panel}

After removing an orphaned page you are taken back to the space's home page. Would be helpful to return to the orphaned page list automatically as it can be annoying when you are trying to remove multiple pages.

Alternatively, some sort of "remove all" or check box could be useful as well.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
