  {panel}

An OpenURL COinS  plugin would provide better-quality bibliographic information to programs that access Confluence pages, like Zotero for Firefox (<http://www.zotero.org/>). Using OpenURL COinS as the method for providing bibliographic information should be easier for Confluence, as COinS data can exist on static pages rather than forcing more work on the webserver (<http://generator.ocoins.info/>).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14455].
  {panel}

Right now we ship Confluence with an english dictionary that is used to build the initial did-you-mean index. Building the initial index takes about 60s on my machine which is quite long. Especially for running acceptance tests this is way to much. One way of making this faster would be to bundle an already indexed english dictionary which then just serves as the initial index. The only drawback is that the index takes up more space in the distribution (66kb vs 2400kb). But I'm not to sure how relevant this is if it saves the customer some time.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14454].
  {panel}

It has turned into quite a mess.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14448].
  {panel}

Add two special values to the "label"/"labels" parameter for blog-posts and contentbylabel macro: @self and @related

@self should use the existing labels of the page/news-item as labels for finding related content. This would provide built-in functionality for the recently created {related-content} usermacro: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONFEXT/Related+Content+User+Macro. If no labels are associated with the page/news-item, then this should default to returning no records (similar to {content-by-label} with no label specified)

@related should leverage the functionality of the {related-labels} macro to choose similar labels based on the page/news-items labels.  It should include the @self labels but also include labels that are associated with labels as part of the content.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Cloud*. Using *Confluence Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFSERVER-14439].
  {panel}

Our confluence is integrated with crowd to manage the users. In crowd we have an internal a read-only ldap directory. 

If we chose the option "external user management", the users in the internal directory are no able to change their name and email (because they are grayed).. If I don't chose the option, the users in the ldap directory are not able to change their "about me" information because confluence complains it can't change the name and mail..

The solution would be to separate the edit profile page in two forms. The first form would be name/mail and would be activated or not depending the "external user management" option and the second form (independent from the previous one) would be always activated.

