When a page is renamed or moved any pages with links are automatically updated. This can cause confusion, as in 'recently updated' and 'version history' the edit is reported as the user who updated the page title, even if they do not have access to the page. Also, it's hard to tell what the edit actually is without going into version history, and even then it's not exactly clear.

It would be great if the edit was registered to something specific like "Confluence Automated Link Updater" and the edit was explained in the version history or as a comment.

