The dynamic task list 2 plugin (version 3.1.1) does not recognize the escape character \ when rendering tasks that contain the underscore character. I have a task that contains underscores in it. The underscores are being interpreted to mean begin/end italics. In order to avoid that behavior, I tried to escape the underscores. However, some of the underscores are being rendered as &#95, as follows.
{noformat}
- task:
Add a symbolic link to the javadocs dir: ln -s /our/dir/structure/for/code/latest-OUR\_<release>\_CM/src/java/docs /top/www/docs/sys/tools\_practices/cm/docs/javadoc/latest-OUR\_<release>\_CM

- rendered task:
Add a symbolic link to the javadocs dir: ln -s /our/dir/structure/for/code/latest-OUR_<release>&#95;CM/src/java/docs /top/www/docs/sys/tools_practices/cm/docs/javadoc/latest-OUR&#95;<release>_CM
{noformat}

