There are several problems when restoring a backup from Confluence 2.5.8 or earlier in to Confluence 2.7 or later.  These usually cause Key violations and fail when trying to restore.

You can usually work around this problem by restoring into 2.6.2 then performing an upgrade to the latest version, so Confluence should present this information to the user when they attempt to upgrade.

