The default number of results returned by the RSS feed settings used throughout Confluence are quite low, causing even users who check their feeds daily to miss posts without realising it. The Feed Burner defaults to only the most recent 10 items from the last 5 days, while the inbuilt feeds in the News spaces cap at 15 items. Whenever a lot of posts are made, or high-volume feeds don't get checked for a day or two, many are silently never picked up by the reader because they're over the feed limit. 

A lot of business users won't know to change these settings when they create the feed, and will still think that they're actually getting everything. As a result, many instances with more than 10 posts per day will have some users who never receive certain news posts.

To address this issue for new users, the default should be lifted to allow a user to go several weeks without checking their feeds, without creating a performance bottleneck. For example, increase the limits to the most recent 100 posts in the past 60 days.

